76561198028204892,Recommended,266010,32794165,Posted: 25 June,all,95th_Iskar,"What a well-crafted little game. Entertaining, increasingly non-trivial puzzles combined with an aesthetically more than pleasing graphical implementation. More than worth its miniscule price."
,Recommended,266010,19276131,"Posted: 25 November, 2015",all,thetick,"A couple of friends recommended this game and I brushed it off because it didn't look all that interesting.  Well it was that and puzzle games tend to be more miss than hit with me.  It went on sale (today actually) for 89 cents and I decided there was nothing to lose.Right away I noticed this game suits me well.  It is very relaxing and easy to jump in and out of.  The puzzles, while they can be tough, are not brain burners, so you can play them after an exhausting day at work and just zone out.  There's also enough to keep you busy for a while.  There are 26 sets with 25 puzzles in each set, which comes out to 650 puzzles to solve.  Not to mention 2 more sets of daily puzzles.  I am almost at three hours in and I already solved 6 sets and today's 2 dailys.  I've noticed that the further in you get, the harder they become.  Still I haven't found myself getting close to frustrated at all and that is a huge plus for me.For these reasons I recommend this game.  I am going to jump back in and get back to the fun."
