,Recommended,266010,23951316,"Posted: 30 June, 2016",all,Zygayga,"Playtime and Time/moneyThis game is actually quite fun, and is great to just toy around with for a few hours at a time, most of my playtime consists with the android version of it, but I have it on steam because I got it through the humble bundle and I am planning on playing just to unlock the achievements to spell out my name on my profile, all in all it's a great game with hours of enjoyment, I don't have an actual rate per hour because most of my time went unrecorded. but you can trust me when I say hours. I mean or you'd just be disregarding my entire review, which is fine too.Exactly what is this game?Puzzle game, you draw lines, you learn the patterns you play challenges and you just unlock new themes, there are hundreds of levels and probably thousands because of the daily challenges which are selected from a pool of a... lot.The dimensions of this game involve drawing lines through points that require up to 4 entries in order to be activated and moving 3 different lines through every point on the board to the other side.It is a lot more difficult than one might think at first and has an amazingly good learning curve, like it felt like I was naturally moving through the game at a very nice pace, and I was learning the best ways to complete puzzles, which do have multiple answers.So now the standard game rating:Story: 0/10(Simply put there is none, but it's a puzzle game, not every one is equipped with a cheesy story to go along with why you're figuring out puzzles.)Gameplay: 10/10 + 📱(addictive, smooth, aesthetic, and highly mobile are ways to describe it, I would suggest getting this on a phone though.)Presentation: 10/10(A minimalist design with a changing theme, and it's always smooth, the game just looks and feels great.)Soundtrack: 7/10(by no means is it a bad sound to the game, however there is no soundtrack and you get a hovering highlight sound everytime you connect a line, but thats all, it's still very smooth and relaxing though and it doesn't get annoying.)Replayability: 10/10(Perfect on the go puzzle game.)"
