,Recommended,266010,19701545,"Posted: 14 December, 2015",all,Thalatte,"Game Visual/AudioThere isn't much can be said about the game's visuals asides from that they're minimalistic. Pretty much the same thing can be said about the game's audio.GameplayThere is no difficulty mode option that's assigned. But each of the puzzles has their own difficult.The objective of this game is rather simple. Is figuring out on how to connect point ""A"" to point ""B."" The lines can't interesect with each other and where as shapes can't intercept each other. However, there's some exception where they can intersect each other.There are two different kinds of sets: Alphabet sets and Daily sets.The alphabet sets has twenty-six sets with twenty-five levels each and it totals out to six hundred fifty levels.The daily sets plays a different than the alphabet sets. Each day there'll be one to three different sets of twenty-five levels to solve. This unique set can be unlocked only after the second set of alphabet is completed. Playing the daily sets unlocks more of the alphabet sets.There's no time limit in this game. Allowing the individual take as much time that they want to solve each of the puzzles.There's a option for color pallet customization section but it's only available after completing the first daily sets. There are plenty of color pallets to chose from but they needed to be unlock first.There thirty-three achievement for this game. Each of these achievements has certain requirements before they can be unlocked.MiscellaneousThere are total of five different trading cards. You only get the three of those cards from the game. There are several ways to get the rest of the trading card: Purchased from Steam's Market; Trade with friends; Booster Packs and it's Booster Pack Creator.Final thoughts, it's an great game to play and enjoy. As for the game's replay value it's low. I would recommend this game but not at the full price.http://store.steampowered.com/app/266010"
