,Recommended,266010,27789869,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,sᵀ ᴬ ᴿ ᴮ ᴼʏ,"It's time to take a break from AAA titles and indulge in the serenity and minimalism of this game. The music score is soothing. The game concept is based on connecting the dots except that it also features color based strokes/ paths and a single stroke is needed to fill each color. The strokes cannot overlap or cross each other. You need to find a path to connect all the boxes of each of the color codes.This is definitely a challenging puzzle otherwise it would have been dull and boring. It's hard but worry not because the pace and learning curve builds up smoothly as you easily navigate few levels in each 'set'. There are as many sets as there are alphabets in the English language. Get those letter achievements to flaunt your showcase. The game also includes Daily sets which are randomly generated but need to be completed for the particular day.You gain skill points as you progress through the sets. The points can be used to unlock many theme colors to suit your comfort and style.Nothing about this game is repetitive. Sometimes there is more than one solution to a puzzle. Now if you are in it only for collecting achievements, then here's aguidefor you lazy peeps. No, I don't use the guide because I prefer to work my brain and not ruin the sanctity of this masterpiece. Besides, it's a wonderful way for me to escape from the mainstream games once in a while. I am not gonna hurry on this one even though I want achievements fast. Take a deep breath and relax.Rated 10/10"
