76561198018683914,Recommended,266010,29909507,Posted: 13 February,all,Carmichael Micaalus,"LYNE is a $3 puzzle game with a simple concept: connect all similar shapes, don't cross the lines.  There are 26 sets (A-Z), and each set has 25 puzzles, totaling to 650 puzzles.  It's also $3.As you progress further in the $3 game, you can unlock a few things, such as different colour pallets, and daily puzzles.  The dailies are randomly generated each day, giving you access to two to three sets (that's 50 to 75 puzzles) on top of the others.  All for $3.I was able to get nearly 24 hours of playtime out of this $3 game, and with the dailies, I can always go back and get a little more play if I so desire.  If you like puzzle games, I highly recommend this game....seriously, it's only $3, you don't even need to wait for a sale; that's cheaper than most fast food meals, and it's less likely to give you the runs."
,Recommended,266010,34348317,Posted: 19 August,all,Melpro Boy,"Lyne is a casual puzzle game created by Thomas Bowker in March 2014. With hundreds of pre-built jigsaw puzzles, your goal is to draw a continuous line that joins together shapes of the same type.It has a minimalist design and a great soundtrack that will make you feel at peace while playing the game. However, later levels will give you some headaches due to the connections, which will require you to resolve the level with multiple lines, shapes and colors.If you are looking for a peaceful puzzle game to play, you need to check this out.Pros- Hundreds of puzzles;- Excellent visual and music;Cons- After a while, puzzles can become repetitive;"
