76561198097987032,Not Recommended,266010,22825865,"Posted: 6 May, 2016",all,erikleppen,"So, why the thumbs-down? On a game with 95% review score?Well, as nice as this game may be, there are a few problems that make me not recommend it to others.1. Lack of varietySure, it has 500 levels. But after 50 or so, you've seen everything. Sure, there may be nodes witheven moreconnections, but it's more of the same, really. The level set names are also quite un-inspired, and the achievements maybe even more so. Also, the unlockable themes are not that much of a novelty either.2. Not learnableThe gameplay itself has a problem too though. It's not learnable. There's not really a way to ""become good"" at this game. Solving levels is merely a case of trying many combinations until you hit the right one. There's a lot of trial and error. Trial and error is usually bad, and I don't see why it's good here.3. Lack of sense of fulfillmentThe third problem is the level solutions themselves. They're too abstract, and don't resemble anything, and after a while, all levels look the same at first glance. Solving a level just doesn't give me that feeling of accomplishment that other puzzles can. When you solve a nonogram, at least you end up with a nice pixel art picture. Here it's just connected shapes - for all levels. It's all a bit too similar.Also, someone could probably write an algorithm to solve these puzzles. :)The game sure has its positives though. I like the minimalist look-and-feel, and I think the font choice and color usage are brilliant. Also it's easy to pick-up and play; it hardly requires a tutorial. It's also a nice original idea to toy around with. It's not a bad game. Certainly not! It's just, well, ...not much more than meets the eye?And it's not overpriced. For 3 dollars it's hard to be disappointed. So sure, pick it up if you think you like it. Just don't expect miracles :)"
