76561197967692485,Recommended,266010,22599552,"Posted: 23 April, 2016",all,^___^,"There's not much to say aboutLYNE. A very straightforward and self-explanatory puzzle game, whose minimalistic visual and audio design is appropriate for relaxing late-night gaming sessions, when all the terrorists are dead and you've run out of zombies to slice. The first few sets will teach you how to play, then the ever-increasing difficulty and complexity will provide a nice challenge for you to tackle at your own pace. Solving the more advanced sets is extremely satisfying, as you will often be required to experiment, think outside the box and come up with new solutions that you hadn't envisioned before. The 26 base sets are nicely complemented by daily challenges of varying difficulty, perfect for a break between harder puzzles or just to keep enjoying the game after you've finished it. A must have."
