,Not Recommended,266010,22785414,"Posted: 3 May, 2016",all,Nuts,"Lyne is a 2d Puzzle game that involves you connecting shapes to each other.Lyne is a simple fun game that you can spend about 10 minutes a day playing and slowly progressing through. If however you are like me and you play games for long periods of time, you will start to hate this game. It becomes pretty frustrating when you can’t figure something out and you just want it to end. It presents itself nicely and allows you the option to change the pallet of the game, customizing it to how you like the visuals. This can make it easier on the eyes at points especially if you are playing at night.I feel like if I had played this differently I would give this a better score. The problem I think this game has it that it is overly long. If it had been only about 10 stages long, I think it would be better. The puzzles are just repetitive and you really end up hating it. The colour pallets are terrible (Despite what I said above) and add nothing to the game at all. It just overstays its welcome. 4/10."
,Recommended,266010,22081178,"Posted: 27 March, 2016",all,Proxykon,"LYNE is an abstract, challenging puzzle game. Connect different shapes from start to finish in order to complete a level.Design & ArtThe design of the game is kept simplistic, basic shapes and a background. Overall the visuals are appealing for a puzzle game, kept basic on intention, because a puzzle game does not really need good graphics.Animations feel fitting and even help you out in some cases (see ""gameplay"" for more info).ControlsLYNE is controlled by mouse. The game gives your an understandable introduction tutorial on how to complete the puzzles.Sound & MusicA soundtrack does not actually exist. It is more like a shallow and eerie electronic synth playing some notes in the background. The soundeffects are nice, but could get repetitive if you play this game for too long. The option to turn the sounds off is available.GameplaySimply put, LYNE is a game consisting of 27 sets á 25 puzzles waiting to be completed. While you start fairly easy, it will get very difficult in later sets. The goal for every puzzle is the same: Connect both of the same shapes with each other by drawing a line between them. You drag the shapes in order to draw the connection. But it is not that easy: Later on, you will need to connect additional shapes with the same line or even multiple shapes at the same time. Another rule is that the connecting lines cannot cross each other. A little animation will hint you, if you try to make that mistake.Besides the alphabetical sets, there is a daily rotation of random puzzles. The rotation starts on easy on mondays and will get progressively higher in difficulty throughout the week. The weekend will use mixed difficulties.An option to change the colors of the game is available, if you gather enough triangles scores for solving sets or daily puzzle sets.WeakpointsWhile LYNE has an actual learning curve, some of the puzzles seem really hard, sometimes trail-and-error was the last resort for me. I rather enjoy games that can be completely solved either through process of elimination or through finding creative solutions, hence I had some times where I put the game down for some time.Also, be aware that this is a puzzle game and thus does not have much additional content. After you completed the main sets, there isn't much left to do besides fulfilling the daily tasks.There only exist certain color schemes, a complete color modification would be much nicer in my opinion.Also, while playing this on different machines, I noticed that your progress and score is saved locally, meaning if you have a laptop and download this game on said laptop while you already played LYNE on your home PC, then your score and progress in the alphabetical sets will NOT transfer.Concluding ThoughtsLYNE is a little but nice, time consuming, challenging but fair puzzle game. The visuals are intentionally kept basic, in order to conform with the gameplay, which is clearly in the foreground here. While the game can look boring and bland, do not let yourself get fooled, this game is one of the teeth-gnashingly types. I can safely recommend this game for yours truly puzzle solver out there. Happy solving!"
