,Recommended,266010,13382999,"Posted: 15 December, 2014",all,Sheila (S-class Log),"Finally 100% completed this game, a lot because the awesome looking letter/pattern achievements that you can display in your showcase on your profile. Yes, I admit that was one of the reasons why I got the game in its first place. But behind all the letters and showcasing there is actually a nice little game, if not 100% when it comes to enjoyment. I will still reccomend it, though, it is a really good game that is not too expensive even when it's not on sale.So what's the good things besides the achievements? The simple concept of connecting shapes, or dots if you want over all the letters in the alphabet  plus extra levels that changes every day (Daily), and a nice bonus that you can change the colour pallette of the background and the shapes. 25 levels per letter set will keep you entertained(or frustrated) throughout the hours, days, week... depending on how fast you complete. There are excellent guides however should you get stuck somewhere. Also, a huge plus for the silence; no annoying music, just the occasional sounds when you connect lines and makes it to the next level.The only downside is the later letter sets when you get the same colour and shapes on every level, sometimes it gets a bit monotonous to do a lot at once. It's getting better once you are closer to the end, though.Looking at both sides of the games, it is a really good one and well worth its price so get it whether it's on sale or not. Not much bad aside from above, either and if those would have had a bit more variety I would probably make huge shoutouts about getting it. Do get it however."
