,Recommended,266010,22866500,"Posted: 8 May, 2016",all,SLUG_GUNNER,"This is an abstract puzzle game.  The objective is to make a line that crosses all shapes.  You get a total of 650 starter puzzles and then daily puzzles (these vary in difficulty depending on the day).  There's not a whole lot to say about this game other than it is very comparable to the phone game ""Flow"", but with way more advanced mechanics than Flow.But the thing is, such a simple puzzle game is just a cover up for an insane cryptography puzzle the developer put in the game as a bonus.  Each time you beat a set you get 1-5 code piece to the puzzle.  There are 999 pieces, which means you have to solve 200 - 999 sets.  The puzzle has been decrypted, however. (solution on the community discussions)My only complaint I had was the palette swaps you unlock as you get points.  Most of them just ain't good because the colors blend with each other too much.  I have not unlocked the last palatte swap but The only ones that are good are the Deep Space and Electro.The achievements are cool too.  (for decorative purposes.. not really challenging at all tho)EDIT:  I got the last palette swap.  Its not good."
