76561198112444032,Recommended,266010,23935651,"Posted: 29 June, 2016",all,Jappy,"LYNE is a visually simplistic and minimalistic puzzle game where you have to connect shapes in certain patterns in order fill the board, similar to the classic game of connect-the-dots. Although it’s quite restricted in its gameplay, the combination of the polished, intuitive interface, conciliating, dynamic audio and simple concept makes this one of the best casual games available on Steam.As you progress further into the game, the puzzles increase in difficulty and complexity, thus, players will ultimately resort to the drawing board on several puzzles. However, even though it’s very limited in terms of its variety, the game never felt tedious or mundane and I was able to appreciate the challenging, yet addictive nature of LYNE, whilst simultaneously solving the ingeniously designed puzzles.Even after completing all the achievements and unlocking all the colour palettes there isn’t really anything to stop you from playing this puzzler. With the addition of 50+ daily puzzles, this game also serves as a pleasurable mental exercise and I would be lying if I said my analytical thinking skills haven’t improved since experiencing LYNE. If you may not know, I don’t hand these out like candy but this game impressed me enough that I’m comfortable giving it a 10/10."
