,Not Recommended,266010,25295752,"Posted: 1 September, 2016",all,AtlasDiesIrae,"TL;DRIt's not that the game itself is badly made, but just the fact that there exists so many other, better, puzzle games on STEAM. I'd describe this game as 6th place in an Olympic race — you wouldn't say that the runner was bad — just that it wasn't as good as the competitors.Blurred LynesThis is definitely a scenario where quantity was put first before quality. There are 650 premade levels (26 ""chapters"" with 25 levels each) but almost all of them feel more or less the same. If you're waiting for a movie to download, then it's a pretty good game to get a level or two in, but it's definitely not a game that you sit down and play for hours, or even 30 minutes, before you're feeling bored.I would've glady traded 500 of those 650 levels for some new gameplay mechanics over time. The existing mechanics are fine, but variety is the spice of life and this game got bland real quick.BreakdownProsBang-for-your-buck: You get a huge amount of levels to play, and you technically get infinite replayability since there are daily new levels.ConsSSDD: The game really doesn't get more interesting time.Score: 4/10 — Would only really recommend picking it up on sale."
