,Recommended,266010,19633879,"Posted: 11 December, 2015",all,HR,Simple puzzle game with cool achievements. Worth buy.
,Recommended,266010,13879189,"Posted: 7 January, 2015",all,𝕼𝖑𝖎𝖝𝖙𝖍𝖊𝖛𝖛𝖎𝖐,"InLYNE's case, a single screenshot is sufficient to get a good a idea of what the game's about.  It's a simple minimalist puzzle game rooted in graph theory.  The puzzles are similar toHamiltonian path problems, with modifications to make things more interesting.  Don't worry if you don't know what I'm talking about; the game has a gentle learning curve.  The puzzles are short (you'll solve some in 5 seconds, and probably stare at others for 5 minutes), but there are 650 of them predefined, and the game procedurally generates more on a daily basis.  It's generally a fun, relaxing game, but can grow challenging and even frustrating at times (in a good way).  Graphics are just lines and soft, solid colors, which works well here, as do the equally soft and minimal musical sound effects.  Given the reasonably low price I highly recommend picking this one up.  You'll have fun while learning something about graph theory (though you may not be aware of the latter)."
