,Recommended,266010,19927723,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,no shirt,"LYNE is a fun, simple, and good-looking puzzle game. I'm normally not a huge fan of straight-up, narrative-less puzzle games, but there was something about LYNE that hooked me from the first time I started it up. It's really smooth, responsive and snappy, and it has a really satisfying set of feedbacks; it seems like it was initially designed for mobile phones, so even with the mouse the interactions feel really tactile. The game is surprisingly challenging. During my average play session I was usually able to clear 6-7 puzzles before I got stuck and had to take a break. It was satisfying to get stuck on a puzzle and then come back to it the next day and solve it immediately. Like most video games, LYNE gets more difficult as it goes on, and the final set of boards is a real challenge. I usually played in the morning, listening to podcasts instead of the game sound. It was a good way to wake up my brain in the morning. I recommend LYNE if you have any interest in puzzle games. Even if you don't normally play puzzle games, you might like this one."
