,Recommended,266010,9700741,"Posted: 1 April, 2014",all,theglowingtoad,"LYNE is a simple game with simple visuals. It's tremendously relaxing but never to the point of putting you to sleep, which some other minimalism inspired puzzlers have been guilty of in the past. Instead, it launches new rules at you through obvious steps, expecting you to flow along with them and disregard the difficulty ramp which climbs higher after each 'set' of puzzles completed. Not to ruin the experience, but you won't notice the change in pace. You'll grow with the game and find your skill improving as the game evolves through mechanics.With that said, it boasts a set of 25 levels for each letter of the alphabet and rewards you with new skins to play the game in... and it's enough. Finally a puzzle game that doesn't feel the need to bombard you with needless 'powerups' for completing level 57 in under a certain time. No, LYNE does something much better and allows you the freedom to explore the puzzles, learn the bits and pieces and relax all at the same time. If you like puzzle games, this is fantastic. If your interests lie with more expansive games that take a good 400+ hours to complete, then LYNE is certainly a great way to wind down at the end of the day.Simple gaming, just like the good ol' days - 9/10"
