76561198067154536,Recommended,266010,16662963,"Posted: 23 June, 2015",all,Punch,"A simple, fun, and challenging game. When describing the game, by saying that you're trying to connect two end points and travel through nodes a particular amount of times, it sounds like it would be boring. The game is designed in such a way that it's so polished and plays so smooth, that it makes that simple idea fulfilling.It's a great way to waste 15 minutes here and there, and there are 550 levels (25*26), and they can be completed in less than 10 seconds, or stump you for a while. You are fortunately able to work on any of the 25 levels at a time, based on what stage (letter of the alphabet) you've gotten to, so that you aren't necessarily going to be stuck on 1 level with nothing else to play. The downside is that you have to wait to beat stage A to get to B, B to get to C, and so forth.The game did go a bit downhill after taking a little too long to boost the difficulty up, and it did feel like it went from medium to hard in a single jump from stage S to stage T (at least in my opinion). I'm now working on stage V and the puzzles tend to take >1 minutes each. I feel like stage T onwards are where this game shines, and it's a shame you have to beat a fair amount of easy puzzles to get there, but that wouldn't stop me from recommending the game."
