,Recommended,266010,10874395,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,nightc1,"This is a fantastic puzzle game about connecting all the same color dots together in lines as well as filling in the non-color specific blocks.  It's a nice little bit of brain training with both fixed levels to work through and daily levels.   The base levels unlock in sets as you complete them as well as do the first two days of daily puzzles.  There are 25 puzzles per set, with 650 puzzles total in the fixed puzzles.   That may sound like a lot, but some puzzles will take seconds to complete while others could take a minute or more so it won't take more than a couple days of regular play to get through them all.  But the daily puzzles tend to add up to another 350 puzzles per week if you play them all.   So even if you blow through the main puzzles in a couple days, there's plenty to come back to.  In addition to all of this there's a sort of meta game of collecting triangles as you play.  Each set is ranked by difficulty with 1 to 5 triangles and if you complete all the puzzles in the set you get those number of triangles added to a master score.   It's not a big thing, but I'm curious to find out what happens at 999 triangles earned out of 999.  I'm about a 120 away from there on the iOS version (so maybe a week and a half more worth of daily puzzles).  It'll take a lot longer on this version since I started it only recently.In any event this game is excellent.  Not many puzzle games get me coming back to them... which makes this a pretty special game.  Plus I don't review games if I don't feel they are worth my time.  This one was more than worth making the effort to post a review."
