76561197995691503,Recommended,266010,10979666,"Posted: 30 June, 2014",all,Lis,I like it! It's a nice challenge for every day ;)
,Recommended,266010,10991127,"Posted: 30 June, 2014",all,Hunniepot,"LYNE is a seemingly simple puzzle game with basic objectives, a multitude of levels, and an euphoric atmosphere.The objectives are simple enough: connect the lines and fill up all of the spaces as you go. As the puzzles progress, different variations in the puzzles create new scenarios, and thus increase the complexity of each puzzle. By completing the puzzle, you progress onward to the next, and so on and so forth. There is no losing in LYNE. There is no time limit, either. You can take as long as you would like to solve each puzzle, and there is no penalty for simply coming back to that puzzle later.In the game, there are 26 levels, ranging from letters A to Z. Each level has sub-levels of 25. This equivalates to 650 puzzles just in the regular game mode alone. However! After completing set A and B (I believe), the player is then allowed access to daily sets. These daily puzzles consist of a version A and B, both having 25 sublevels in them. That's another 50 new puzzles per day. These puzzles range in difficulty and are completely random. With a staggering number of 700+ puzzles in just a week, there is plenty to do on LYNE.Not only is there no pressure for you to whiz by the game, but there is also a very calming and entracing soundtrack that accompanies you as you play. With each movement of the puzzle pieces, there are tones that mix together and with the soundtrack to create some really beautiful, relaxing music. Not only is this music a nice stress-reliever, but there is an actual science behind it. The ambient noises actually promote brainwave activity, thus amplifying a better mood, problem-solving, cognition, and much more. But, hey, who doesn't like to just hear something nice playing in the background?All in all, LYNE is a fantastic game that can be played by any one of any age. Not too mention it is affordable at only $2.99 (about $0.75 with a coupon). It's a great way to relax after a long day at work, decompress after some stressful online match, or just to simply pass the time. If you haven't played it already, I strongly recommend that you do. It is really a gem that will have you hooked!10/10"
