,Recommended,266010,11971320,"Posted: 3 September, 2014",all,Dark Blue Monkey,"Lyne is a very satisfying puzzler game.  The game, effectively, is to find a route through all the nodes on a grid, such that ""router"" nodes are used the stipulated number of times.   Colourful, relaxing, and very very satisfying.Most levels have multiple solutions, which grants a very rewarding gameplay.  Most of the levels can be solved with about 10 seconds of observation, and about 5 seconds of swiping.  There are some, however, which require far more consideration.  The longest I spent was about half an hour trying and re-trying paths through the level, until I ended up giving up and cheating, using a hint online.    Other than that one slip, the rest of the game was quite solvable with patience.Perfectly suited to casual gaming, I left the game minimized, until my tea breaks, when I'd do a level or two.    There are hundreds and hundreds of levels, and with daily levels offering a ""quick fix"", there's a lot of enjoyment packed into this little puzzler.Highly recommended for anyone who likes things like Sudoku, or quick crosswords.. i.e. that short, quick puzzle fix."
,Recommended,266010,12043878,"Posted: 10 September, 2014",all,NotMike,"Honestly, there are not many puzzle games that I like. They are very limited because not only do the hard ones make me feel incredibly dumb, but I also just am not easily sucked into puzzle games.This one sucked me in.Within 2 hours, I felt very happy with my purchase. This game is very addictive, fun and enjoyable. The fact that the mechanics are very self-explanatory and easy to expand on make for great gameplay as you are constantly facing surprisingly difficult challeneges. For example, I was playing one of the daily challenges, which features 25 generated puzzles that are completely new, and for the first half, I thought ""This is really easy"". After that though, I was spending a good 15 - 20 minutes on each level. This game goes from real easy to really challenging very quickly, but for whatever reason, the way it is done doesn't make you feel stupid. You still feel like you are progressing.Basically, this game is worth the purchase. It has nice sounds and the game is easy to get into. I certainly recommend this game as a very good, if not fantastic puzzle game.(Plus, there's at least 650 puzzles, plus all the daily puzzles, so you will have more than enough gameplay)"
