,Recommended,266010,13115656,"Posted: 27 November, 2014",all,Vistorn **Read my Profile**,"LYNE takes a very simple concept and expands upon it drastically, it's amazing to see how fleshed out some of the levels in the game get.  To begin you're giving one different colour and you're tasked to get it to connect to the other end piece while lighting up all of the same colours similtainiously, sounds easy right? Well it gets far more complicated, they begin to introduce blocks which need to be activated a certain amount of times and different colours which can't be crossed over, the puzzels get quite challenging later on.  It's somewhat addictive, I personally either found myself breezing through some levels or getting suck figuring out how to get that damn fith diamond lit up.  Either way, if you're plowing through levels like a bat out of hell or stuck figuring out how to finish a puzzel correctly the sense of satifaction you get from completeing a level, is quite thrilling.  The implimentation of daily levels for people who just can't get their fill of making lines is quite cute.  Not to mention the ambient music makes it all the more calming an experience. And the graphical makes it much easier to recognize what it is you should be focusing on. Reccomened for anyone who needs a few hours to just chill out, it's relatively inexpensive and it'll get the job done and then some, although it may not be everyone's cup of tea, especially if you're some sort of action junkie I can't see you getting much of a thrill out of connecting lines."
