,Recommended,266010,17134061,"Posted: 19 July, 2015",all,Vino [Olive Garden],"This puzzle game has a really bizarre difficulty curve. Most games start out easy and get harder - Lyne starts out extremely easy (like, click and drag in a straight line to solve the ""puzzle"" - 15 times in a row) and then gets enormously hard for certain levels, and then goes back to being completely brain-dead easy, then fiendishly difficult again.As a game, it's perfectly good. Cool mechanic, interesting puzzles, lots of little twists on it, an enormous amount of content (though a good deal of that content is repetitions of simple concepts to make sure you understand a new twist). Recommended for puzzle fans who aren't super dumb.Addendum to this review: I am basically ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ so ""game hard"" complaints from me should be taken with a grain of salt."
,Recommended,266010,14447383,"Posted: 13 February, 2015",all,❄ ViaVio ❄,LYNE
,Recommended,266010,14663118,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,LonM,"LYNE is a fun and addictive puzzle game. It doesn't try and dress itself up in a story, like some other puzzle games i've seen, which is definitely a plus. You just start it up and play.The basic premise is to fill the ""board"", drawing lines between nodes and switches, except you can't cross the lines. It's kind of like sewing buttons, but on a digital canvas. Complete a set of 25 to earn points. It is fairly simple to play, but as levels increase the solutions become much more complex, and like most puzzles, take breaks. Otherwise things can get very frustrating.This game is mouse controlled, but I've found streaming it to a mobile device to be quite a fun experience as well.The graphics in this game are very minimal and simplistic, and you can unlock new backgrounds as you earn points. This is good, as it helps set the focus on the puzzle. Similarly, the sound design in this game is very simplistic, but well done.There is pretty much no limit to this game (at least none that I have found). There are new ""daily puzzles"" that are generated, well, daily to keep you playing as well as a mysterious ""???"" puzzle that you can start to decode after you earn enough points.This is a very good game if you like puzzles, just be sure to pace yourself."
76561198104807979,Recommended,266010,13701470,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,Dallasflett,"Rating: 10/10Unneccesary quote: ""Connect the dots just got way more badass""Why?:So during the steam sales I was selling all of my cards just trying to get another dollar towards a game.I had bought alot of games, and only bought this on a whim, thinking to myself ""Can't hurt, if it's crap, I got a lot more games to play"".And boy am I regrettful for my attitude prior to playing this game.The game works for both casual players just looking to kill some time before going out, and those serious players who want to solve every last puzzle their brain power can possibly muster.It's a simple idea that gets really challenging (and I mean REALLY challenging). Your goal is to connect the dots. Easy as that may sound, more dot's come along and you start getting confused, wondering whether this line goes here, or there. It feels so rewarding to solve a level you had been working on for a half hour.The sound effects are easy-going, making it easy (and ideal) to listen to your own personal soundtrack.Lyne is game that is incredibly addicting (steam didn't get my hours logged in right) and stands among one of the best games I've bought this holiday.And I bought it for just a dollar."
