,Recommended,266010,22473365,"Posted: 17 April, 2016",all,TheWorstAmy,"This game is everything written on the box.  It's a puzzler with a concept that sounds relatively simple at first - just connect a line of shapes from beginning to end - but the more you play, the more the game throws at you, the more shapes you have to connect, and the more crossroads you're given, until this once simple game curiously grows difficult enough for you to have to wrack your brain around everything you know just to solve a single puzzle.  It's an eventually infuriating but ultimately satisfying experience to be able to complete.The music, as stated, is also intentionally calming.  The background pads drone as each connection is audibly accentuated with a soft syntheized pop.  It's minimal, but that's the point, and it's destressing enough to make up for those moments where you can't seem to make the right connection.  Think of the game Flow Free turned up to eleven and a soundtrack turned down to ""chill out"" and you have a game I would recommend to any fan of puzzle games."
