,Recommended,266010,14860401,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,PhazonMadness,"I found this game by complete happenstance. I've noticed for a few months that a few users spell out a word or phrase on their Steam profile using the images of the achievements unlockable in the game. I decided to humor the idea of seeing what kind of game this would be, and I've been left nothing short of amazed.The concept is rather simple: Create lines between like shapes, and don't intersect others. It's a bit more complicated than that later on, but that's the jist of it. The lack of a soundtrack, only accompanied by chimes and soft sounds, is beautiful. The basic color scheme, and calm graphical design, create an immediately calming presense. The level design is something else. While some are incredibly easy, others will almost certainly impede your progress, but without leaving the bitter taste of a poor puzzle. I found that each harder puzzle was only one or two mouse clicks away from being correct, and completing such a puzzle leaves a pleasant aftertaste. Not to mention the seductive chime that plays after every completed level.I haven't played terribly far into the game, but I've realized just how clever, how beautiful it really is. I tend to find solace in video games after a long day, and lately, my only interest has been to complete more puzzles here! This is a fantastic game, a great stress reliever, and for whatever reason is incredibly useful in spelling words on your Steam wall!"
