,Recommended,266010,16529823,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,Insta,"It may be an Unity game ripped right out of the mobile version without even adding a Quit button on the main menu, but it's got a great concept.Connect point A to point B, and eventually more points to other points, at the same time that all the parts of the level have to have been used to their full extent in order to win.The game has 26 level sets, one for each letter in the alphabet, which also gives you achievements for it. I guess you could use them to spell out words like one of the people in the featured reviews said. There's also a daily level set unlocked once you beat the two first level sets, so even if you finish the game, you have more to do if you're bored.For the cheap price it's at, I guess it's worth it. The first levels are pretty easy, but on Level Set C it starts going up way higher.If you like having that ""Ahaaaa...!"" moment when you finally realize what you did wrong, get the game.If you hate effort, and love hacking in FPS games to feel like you're the best, ♥♥♥♥ off and go back to your Call of Duty."
