,Not Recommended,266010,23110134,"Posted: 20 May, 2016",all,Gilamex,"I only bought it for the achievement showcase, like everyone always talks about, and for three dollars, sure it's a good deal.I'm not recommending this, however, because it just goes on for way too long. WAY too long. ""You unlocked a skin."" ...Wow thanks... just... something for me to do to not get so bored with the same stuff I've been doing for the past several levels... The main reason I rate this down is because there's 26 levels or ""areas"" (one for each letter of the alphabet) and in each of those, there's about 30--THIRTY--sublevels. After level ""C"" you already are introduced to all the game's mechanics and all the new challenging obstacles. After that it's over 350 levels of just the same stuff. I remember sitting here for nearly 8 hours playing just to get to ""S"". It's so monotonous and boring you'll want to kill yourself like me. I understand it's supposed to be ""peaceful"" or ""serene"" but after the first 5 letters, I just got bored and looked up a walkthrough to speedrun the game. It almost got even more annoying at that point just because you had to wait for the end of the letter level and just... ugh.RATING REASON:Come on, thirty levels in each letter? I mean, that's perfectly fine. Nice amount of content, I suppose. But you HAVE to introduce new mechanics. You just HAVE to. You are introduced to the last game mechanic in the third letter level. You just can't repeat the same mechanics for 690 levels. (Yes I did the math. 30 x 23). Don't waste your time unless you honestly have the patience.Seven hundred and eighty levels of the same damn thing... Good god..."
,Recommended,266010,9537524,"Posted: 17 March, 2014",all,Prostetnic Vogon Jeltz,"Incredible mellow-but-brainbending puzzler. Just unlocked 'Set C' (& theFREE'Daily Levels') and am already hooked!The premise is simple: draw lines to connect blocks of the same colour, with a specific start- & end-point for each line. Later levels have intersections thatmustbe used a specific number of times for a successful completion.LYNE quickly gets pretty fiendish & you'll be back-tracking as you try to (ornotto) cross lines in the right/wrong places. It's a fairly simple task to reset your line though - or even to just remove a 'bad link'.Accompanied by a chilled-out soundtrack, the in-game bleeps & bloops merge with the music to form a soothing audio experience.At a wallet-friendly £1.99 (& currently £1.33 on promotion), LYNE is an absolutemust-havefor any fan of the genre!10/10"
