,Recommended,266010,17014659,"Posted: 12 July, 2015",all,somnomania,"This game is so much more than the trailer and screenshots can convey. Yes, it's a game where you connect shapes with single lines, but it goes so astronomically far beyond that. I can't even properly explain how the problem solving ends up working on each level; it's that fluid and intuitive. You just... start with one color and then try other colors until it works, and there's process of elimination and trial and error and each level completed is a soothing, peaceful little tidbit of satisfaction. The very early levels provide a good example of this game's whole vibe, with gameplay hints disguised in three or four words that you have to look at in relation to the current level and what you need to do. That's hard to explain too, I'm not doing it well. Lyne is calming and focusing at the same time, and I would have gladly paid full price for it. Heck, I would've happily paid like ten bucks for it if it was that price and I had a chance to try it out first. Do yourself a favor, even if you're not a huge fan of puzzle games, and buy this game. Also buy copies for everyone you know, if it's on sale. 11/10 excellent flawless game."
