,Recommended,266010,15457809,"Posted: 19 April, 2015",all,RedDreadnaught,"Lyne is an excellent pure puzzler that challenges your spacial awareness.  No quick reflexes or special items required.  No in-game purchases.  Relaxing visual layout and sound effects.  It's one of the best kinds of puzzle games in which you figure out how to play in minutes (thanks to a simple tutorial set), and can find yourself playing for hours to get just one more level completed.  All you do is create lines to connect like-colored shapes together.  The challenge involves passing through various hubs and not crossing over any lines you've already drawn.  If you need to start over, you just click on any shape to erase any lines previously drawn from that point.  For those who like Steam achievements, you get one for every set of 25 puzzles you complete, plus there are random daily sets.  Lyne is a highly addictive and satisfying mental workout."
