,Recommended,266010,12471112,"Posted: 12 October, 2014",all,Pascal,"What is LYNE? It's a game about associating lines. It seems simple, but like most puzzle games, the more you advance, the harder it gets. I love LYNE. Why is that? Well, I like the way it's simple, but at the same time intelligent. The game is addictive and you will find yourself coming back to challenge your brain. The art is simplistic, but it fits the game just right. You can change it as you advance with smooth combinations of colors. It's simple and intelligent just like the game. There is not much music, when you interact with the levels, sound comes out of your interactions. Sometimes it can create an appeasing melody. The goal is just to relax your mind, while at the same time working it.In LYNE, you have two options, to play the pre-built levels which go from A to Z with 25 levels in each (650 levels, if you feel lazy) or do the dailies which are levels generated everyday for you to play. You guessed right, the longevity of the game isn't bad. While LYNE is a mobile port, it is a good one. Both are the same things, except for the Steam features (achievements and cards).I highly recommend LYNE for everyone who would like a game that chills your mind, but exercises it at the same time."
,Recommended,266010,10868081,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,theotherwinchester,"At the price of 74 cents, this is definitely worth buying. It's relaxing as heckie and it's also engaging in that you do get achievements, and with the daily puzzles that you unlock after completing Set A, I think, there are always more puzzles for you to solve. The pallet can be changed as soon as you unlock more pallets, and I think that's pretty rad. Totally worth buying while it's on sale."
,Recommended,266010,10948720,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,GRekoAssassino,The best puzzle game ever made!
,Recommended,266010,12532634,"Posted: 17 October, 2014",all,jimothyjim,"Great puzzle game. Simple to understand but hard to master. A video or even image will make much clearer sense than a text descrpiton will but basically there is at least 1 shape on each level. There is a start point, and an end point, and you have to draw lines from one to the other and make sure to connect every corresponding shape along the way. At the same time you can't overlap any lines, there's normally more than one shape, and each non shape on the board (junctions basically) have to have the correct number of lines travelling through them.There's good levels of difficulty, very easy to very hard, and a good number of puzzles. There's also at least 1 daily puzzle for you to complete, so you can invest plenty of time into it, as my hours on record suggest. Easily worth the money on sale or at full price."
