,Recommended,266010,13954335,"Posted: 12 January, 2015",all,A Penguin,"A puzzle game where the objective is to connect all shapes of similar shape/color along finite number of lines. LInes cannot cross, but some shapes will accept any line color and can accept a line multiple times.That's it.Pros:+ Easy to pick up+ Gets gradually difficult+ You will not run out of levels, because the game generates daily puzzles+ There's like 650 pre-built puzzles anyway, this game will take you at least 10 hours+ Steam trading cards+ The achievements are letters, and you can use them to spell things in your steam achievement showcase. If you're bad at puzzles, you can just look at one of the many walkthroughs and enjoy your ill-gotten showcase; nobody will know.+ Costs less than a couple of tacos+ Soothing fluteCons:-Points of note:? No soundtrack (there is audio as you interact with the pieces and finish stages), but this lets you put on any kind of ambient music that you want. This would be a con, but I don't think it's reasonable to expect this game to have a 10+ hour soundtrack.? It's a puzzle game, so if you don't like puzzle games, don't buy it.? CasualEdit: After beating the game (all the puzzles and some of the random daily ones) I can't say this game was mind-bendingly difficult, but I did get stuck on a few levels from time to time. The solution to that was usually to just go away and do somthing else and then come back to the puzzle with a fresh mind after a day or a few."
