,Recommended,266010,21987978,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,Sneaky,"I got this game for less than a dollar with a coupon and I'm shocked with how much time I've spent playing it. The puzzles are simple and can be completed very quickly if you can see the solution, but as you press on, some of them turn into real stumpers. It's probably best that I don't try to explain how the puzzles work here, so check out the video on the store page.There is plenty of content here. There are 26 sets of 25 puzzles each, (as far as I know - I'm still only about halfway through the alphabet!) that makes 650 puzzles in the core game. On top of that, there are new randomly generated sets avaliable every day, so even when you've completed the core sets you can continue playing new puzzles at various difficulties. New color schemes gradually unlock as you complete sets. Given the game's price, it's a worthwhile game even if you don't have the dedication to plow through the entire thing. There's also some sort of ARG going on, which isn't really my thing, but seems cool enough.Definitely recommended if you enjoy puzzle/logic games or spelling out profanity on your profile with the achievement showcase."
