,Recommended,266010,21721821,"Posted: 8 March, 2016",all,Redbeard,"I wasn't expecting much from LYNE, as it is a simple-looking affair.However, it turns out that it is quite a good puzzle game, with various brain teasers.I sailed through a lot of them in the A and B sets, and was thinking ""This is too easy"", but then there were two in the B set that I had to puzzle over for a while.When you finish the A and B sets, you unlock the daily challenges - and some of those can be complex to figure out.Am yet to start the C-Z sets.If they get progressively harder, then I might be in trouble.Good exercise for the brain.Update:Have now completed the G series. It does get a bit harder, but I have found that if I get stuck on one, if I come back to it later I can often finish it within a minute (which goes to show what a fresh look at a problem will do).However, after solving the first few hundred puzzles, it does get a bit boring.Therefore, it is probably best to play the game every few days or so, rather than try to do it all in sequential days."
